## Reuse
- In this repo:
  - `packages/core/src/dependencies.ts` is the clean injection point for swapping the fetch implementation.
  - `packages/core/src/extract.ts` already has `FetchExecutionHooks.onStatusChange`; extend this area into a richer progress abstraction rather than bolting progress logic directly into the adapters.
  - `packages/pi-smart-fetch/src/index.ts` already renders coarse statuses and can reuse the same row model if the core starts emitting truer phases.
- In upstream `wreq`:
  - `ClientBuilder.connect_timeout()` and `ClientBuilder.read_timeout()` show that connect/read phase distinction already exists.
  - `ClientBuilder.connection_verbose()` and `src/client/conn/verbose.rs` provide an existing path for lower-level I/O visibility.
  - `TlsInfo` and `HttpInfo` show that some connection metadata is already attached to response extensions and could be surfaced by the fork.

